<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 05 at 9:03AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Meriwether, northwestern Talbot and eastern Harris Counties through
930 AM EDT...
At 903 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Cataula, or near
Hamilton, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Manchester, Pine Mountain, Waverly Hall, Warm Springs,
Woodland, Ellerslie, F.d. Roosevelt State Park, Cataula, Flint Hill
and Mulberry Grove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
